post_cb({"37905447": {"ParentId": "37905409", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_37905409_37905447_0\">Is this reflective of what might make it into the standard?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>From the working draft (<a href=\"http://eel.is/c++draft/optional#optional.syn-1\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">[20.5.2/1]</a>):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_37905409_37905447_1\">A program that necessitates the instantiation of template\u00a0optional\u00a0for a reference type [...]\u00a0is ill-formed.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I guess this replies to your question.</p>\n<p>Note that you can still work around it by using <code>std::reference_wrapper</code>, as mentioned by @bobah in the comments.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "4987285", "LastEditorUserId": "4987285", "LastEditDate": "2017-10-12T12:19:05.850", "Id": "37905447", "Score": "8", "CreationDate": "2016-06-19T08:46:54.417", "LastActivityDate": "2017-10-12T12:19:05.850"}, "37905409": {"CommentCount": "5", "AcceptedAnswerId": "37905447", "CreationDate": "2016-06-19T08:41:28.533", "LastActivityDate": "2017-10-12T12:19:05.850", "PostTypeId": "1", "ViewCount": "579", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Will std::experimental::optional<> support references?", "Id": "37905409", "Score": "11", "Body": "<p>At the moment, <code>boost::optional&lt;&gt;</code> supports references but the <code>std::experimental::optional&lt;&gt;</code> on my system from libstdc++ does not. Is this reflective of what might make it into the standard?</p>\n<p>I know that the optional proposal author spun off optional references as a separate proposal so that the main optional proposal would have a better chance of being accepted. Was the proposal for optional references rejected or did work on it stop?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++-standard-library><c++1z>", "OwnerUserId": "1128289", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_37905409_37905447_1": {"section_id": 196, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_37905409_37905447_1": {"section_id": 190, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_37905409_37905447_1": {"section_id": 5015, "quality": 1.0, "length": 7}}}});